<h2>monitor</h2>
    <p>This attribute can only be used to modify class and category, which means that class objects generated by the current class can use the synchronized lock mechanism. For example: </p>
    <pre class="code">
component Demo
{
    бнбн
    [uuid(27628ac4-fdd2-48d0-94ff-3033f99b1e60), <b>monitor</b>]
    class CDemo {
        бнбн
    }
}
</pre>
    <p></p>
    <p>When component using this attribute, the client program can invoke the <a class="style1" href="../inline_func/MyCMonitorPart.htm">MyCMonitorPart</a> method to obtain class smart pointer <a class="style1" href="../../../zee/class/CMonitorRef.htm">CMonitorRef</a>, using all methods in class <a class="style1" href="../../../zee/class/CMonitor.htm">CMonitor</a>.</p>
    <p>This attribute can be used with other attributes.</p>
